<p>Speaking to Metro.co.uk earlier this month, the mother said: 'I started making the food to catch the interest of my [picky] daughter.' Pictured, an egg dish made to look like Cogsworth from Beauty and the Beast</p>

<p>She added: 'The inspiration is to look at the ingredients and think of a character.' Pictured, Toy Story's Mr. Potato Head made from a burger-type dish</p>

<p>Toy Story's much-loved Hamm impressively created with only the use of two fried eggs and some pieces of salad</p>

<p>And it's not only famous movie characters that get a seat at the mother's table, with the parent also creating animal-themed meals (above)</p>

